column10: Vehicles approaching crosswalk cannot see around parked cars to notice pedestrians and it can be hard for pedestrians to see oncoming traffic. You have to kind of peek out around the cars to get started sometimes.

Cars racing down Zion Drive completely ignoring the existence of the pedestrian crosswalk on the brow of the hill by the swimming pool, used by dog walkers, school children, those walking for exercise, etc.
